organic_results.title: Interaction and prestige of secondary school teachers in the Province of Ontario
organic_results.snippet: Four hundred and twenty-six randomly selected Ontario secondary school teachers rated 75 subject teaching positions on a prestige status scale. Teachers of academic, technical, and commercial subjects agreed that a prestige status hierarchy of teaching positions existed. Academic subjects were accorded highest prestige followed by commercial and then technical subjects.
